      "content": "wait, \"unauthorized external party\"? the logs show it wasn't even an external attack, it was just an open bucket sitting there for three days because of a config error. won't it look really suspicious if a tech journalist or a security researcher digs into the logs and sees there was actually no \"unauthorized party\" involved, just a mistake on our part? wouldn't that make us look way worse if we're caught lying about it being an attack?",
